                    "value": "Row-Level Security: Area_Litho",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontWeight": "bold",
                      "fontSize": "14pt",
                      "color": "#FFFFFF"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Role: Area_Litho. Table filter on dim_equipment: [area] = \"Litho\". Propagation: dim_equipment sits on the one side of a single-direction relationship into fact_lot_movement, so this filter restricts every fact-based measure (Queue Hours, Process Hours, Holds Count, Scrap Units, Tool Process Hours, and WIP measures) to Litho-tool activity. It does NOT restrict dim_lot, dim_product, or dim_step directly, since filters cannot flow backward up a many-to-one relationship without bidirectionality, which this model intentionally avoids. Full lot-level isolation would require either a bidirectional relationship or a second RLS filter directly on dim_lot."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
